= Memory Component =

[[TOC]]

== Functions ==

|| ( ) ||  `Memory::allocate(size)` || ''Allocate local memory'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::deallocate(buffer)` || ''De-allocate local memory'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::begin_group(group)` || ''Begin allocating memory associated with the given group''||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::end_group(group)` || ''End allocating memory associated with the given group'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::curr_group()` || ''Return name of the current group'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::current([group])` || ''Current number of local bytes allocated'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::available([group])` || ''Estimate of amount of local memory left'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::efficiency([group])` || ''Estimate of ratio of current local usage to local available'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::highest([group])` || ''Maximum number of local bytes allocated for group'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::set_limit(size [,group])` || ''Set limit on number of local bytes available'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::get_limit([group])` || ''Get limit on number of local bytes available'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::num_allocate([group])` || ''Return the number of calls to allocate for the group'' ||
|| ( ) ||  `Memory::num_deallocate([group])` || ''Return the number of calls to deallocate for the group'' ||
== Parameters ==

|| ( ) || `limit_available` || ''Set limit on the number of local bytes available for dynamic memory'' ||
|| ( ) || `efficiency_threshold` || ''Set efficiency threshold before displaying a warning message'' ||
|| ( ) || `fill_after_allocate` || ''Value to fill memory after it's allocated'' ||
|| ( ) || `fill_before_deallocate` || ''Value to fill memory before it's deallocated'' ||
|| ( ) || `tracking` || ''Set memory tracking on or off.  Turning off resorts to native new[]/delete[].' ||

== Exceptions ==

|| ( ) || `ExceptionBadMemoryAllocate` || ''Error while allocating memory'' ||
|| ( ) || `ExceptionBadMemoryDeallocate` || ''Error while deallocating memory'' ||

